âœ… STEP 1 â€” Install Socket.IO in Angular

Go to your Angular project root and run:

npm install socket.io-client

âœ… STEP 2 â€” Create a Socket Service

In Angular, all real-time logic should go inside a service, not inside components.

Run:

ng generate service services/socket


This will create:

src/app/services/socket.service.ts

âœ… STEP 3 â€” Setup Namespaces Inside the Service

Now open socket.service.ts and add this:

import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';
import { io, Socket } from 'socket.io-client';

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class SocketService {

  private orbitalSocket!: Socket;
  private rpsSocket!: Socket;

  constructor() { }

  // ----------------------------
  // ORBITAL ALLIANCE NAMESPACE
  // ----------------------------
  connectOrbital() {
    this.orbitalSocket = io("http://192.168.29.24:3000/orbital");

    this.orbitalSocket.on("connect", () => {
      console.log("Connected to ORBITAL namespace:", this.orbitalSocket.id);
    });
  }

  getOrbitalSocket() {
    return this.orbitalSocket;
  }

  // ----------------------------
  // RPS NAMESPACE
  // ----------------------------
  connectRPS() {
    this.rpsSocket = io("http://192.168.29.24:3000/rps");

    this.rpsSocket.on("connect", () => {
      console.log("Connected to RPS namespace:", this.rpsSocket.id);
    });
  }

  getRPSSocket() {
    return this.rpsSocket;
  }
}

âœ” You now have two separate connections:

/orbital

/rps

Both independent.

âœ… STEP 4 â€” Use the Service Inside Components

Now you will create two Angular components:

OrbitalGameComponent
RpsGameComponent

ðŸŸ¦ STEP 4A â€” ORBITAL GAME COMPONENT

Generate:

ng generate component components/orbital-game


Open:

orbital-game.component.ts


Add:

import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { SocketService } from '../../services/socket.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-orbital-game',
  templateUrl: './orbital-game.component.html'
})
export class OrbitalGameComponent implements OnInit {

  socket: any;

  constructor(private socketService: SocketService) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.socketService.connectOrbital();
    this.socket = this.socketService.getOrbitalSocket();

    this.listenForUpdates();
  }

  listenForUpdates() {
    this.socket.on("updatePlayers", (players: any) => {
      console.log("Orbital Players:", players);
    });

    this.socket.on("updateProjectiles", (projectiles: any) => {
      console.log("Orbital Projectiles:", projectiles);
    });
  }

  startGame() {
    this.socket.emit("initGame", {
      username: "Player123",
      width: 1024,
      height: 576
    });
  }

  shoot(angle: number) {
    this.socket.emit("shoot", {
      x: 100,
      y: 100,
      angle
    });
  }
}


Done. Orbital Game now fully works inside Angular.

ðŸŸ© STEP 4B â€” RPS GAME COMPONENT

Generate:

ng generate component components/rps-game


Open:

rps-game.component.ts


Add:

import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { SocketService } from '../../services/socket.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-rps-game',
  templateUrl: './rps-game.component.html'
})
export class RpsGameComponent implements OnInit {

  socket: any;

  constructor(private socketService: SocketService) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.socketService.connectRPS();
    this.socket = this.socketService.getRPSSocket();

    this.listenEvents();
  }

  listenEvents() {
    this.socket.on("newGame", (data: any) => {
      console.log("Room created:", data.roomId);
    });

    this.socket.on("result", (data: any) => {
      console.log("Match result:", data.winner);
    });
  }

  createGame() {
    this.socket.emit("createGame");
  }

  joinGame(roomId: string) {
    this.socket.emit("joinGame", { roomId });
  }

  sendChoice(choice: string, roomId: string) {
    this.socket.emit("p1Choice", { roomId, choice });
  }
}


Now RPS works perfectly inside Angular, fully isolated from the Orbital namespace.

âœ… STEP 5 â€” Add These Components to HTML

Example route:

<!-- orbital-game.component.html -->
<button (click)="startGame()">Start Orbital Game</button>


Example route:

<!-- rps-game.component.html -->
<button (click)="createGame()">Create RPS Room</button>

